<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,401,1339,1365]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
Records from 
<collectingCountry box="[337,401,1339,1365]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">India</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[422,623,1339,1365]" country="India" name="Maharashtra" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">MAHARASTRA</collectingRegion>
: Nagpur— 
<bibRefCitation author="Visvesvara, G." box="[753,968,1339,1366]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="435 - 443" refId="ref14201" refString="Visvesvara, G. (1963) On some Gastrotricha from India with description of two new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6, 435 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936308651379" type="journal article" year="1963">Visvesvara (1963)</bibRefCitation>
; GENERAL RECORD— 
<bibRefCitation author="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C." pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="169" refId="ref12873" refString="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C. (2004) Gastrotricha. In: Fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Zoological Survey of India, Kol- kata, pp. 169." type="book chapter" year="2004">Naidu &amp; Rao (2004)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,566,1411,1437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Habitat (as in Indian records).</emphasis>
Freshwater; among freshwater aquatic weeds with attached muds in shallow part of tanks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,524,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" box="[199,524,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1483,1509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Distribution.</emphasis>
Cosmopolitan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was found in 
<collectingCountry box="[613,671,1519,1545]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">India</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Visvesvara, G." box="[713,921,1519,1546]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="435 - 443" refId="ref14201" refString="Visvesvara, G. (1963) On some Gastrotricha from India with description of two new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6, 435 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936308651379" type="journal article" year="1963">Visvesvara (1963)</bibRefCitation>
. According to the author, the specimens agree with data reported in literature for the species except for the lower number of furcal segments (17 vs 22). Mormetric details were not provided for the 10 studied specimens. However, on the basis of the scale bar it is possible to establish some measures of the drawn specimen, which are as follows: total length, 244 μm, pharynx length, 35 μm, and furca length 67 μm. Based on these measurements, the sketched specimen appears much smaller than specimens recorded from other geographic places (Total length 300-500 μm, pharynx length 40-90 μm, furca length 60-150 μm; data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwank, P." box="[318,487,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref13700" refString="Schwank, P. (1990) Gastrotricha. In: Braur, A., Schwoerbel, J. &amp; Zwick, P. (Eds.), Susswasser Fauna von Mitteleuropa. Band 3. Heft 1. 2. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart and Jenai, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 262." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<bibRefCitation author="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C." box="[199,436,1771,1798]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="169" refId="ref12873" refString="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C. (2004) Gastrotricha. In: Fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Zoological Survey of India, Kol- kata, pp. 169." type="book chapter" year="2004">Naidu &amp; Rao (2004)</bibRefCitation>
mention much smaller specimens (up to 200 μm in total length) from Nagpur, but it is unclear if these are the same specimens reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Visvesvara, G." box="[735,939,1807,1834]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="435 - 443" refId="ref14201" refString="Visvesvara, G. (1963) On some Gastrotricha from India with description of two new species. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 6, 435 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936308651379" type="journal article" year="1963">Visvesvara (1963)</bibRefCitation>
or new specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1339,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
Regardless, based on the available information, the presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Voigt" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[931,1090,1843,1869]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Polymerurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="nodicaudus">
<emphasis box="[931,1090,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">P. nodicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1187,1843,1869]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">India</collectingCountry>
should be considered solely provisional. Future data from fresh material should confirm of disprove the presence of this morphospecies in 
<collectingCountry box="[182,243,1915,1941]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">India</collectingCountry>
. Population genetic studies could challenge the reported cosmopolitan distribution of this taxon (see the preliminary work by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanneby, T. &amp; Todaro, M. A. &amp; Jondelius, U." box="[388,615,1951,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="185 - 202" refId="ref12197" refString="Kanneby, T., Todaro, M. A. &amp; Jondelius, U. (2012) A phylogenetic approach to species delimitation in freshwater Gastrotricha from Sweden. Hydrobiologia, 683, 185 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10750 - 011 - 0956 - 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kånneby 
<emphasis box="[496,546,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
and also 
<bibRefCitation author="Magpali, L. &amp; Machado, D. R. P. &amp; Araujo, T. Q. &amp; Andre, R. S. &amp; Garraffoni, R. S." box="[722,945,1951,1978]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" pagination="62 - 93" refId="ref12737" refString="Magpali, L., Machado, D. R. P., Araujo, T. Q., Andre, R. S. &amp; Garraffoni, R. S. (2021) Long distance dispersal and pseudo-cryptic species in Gastrotricha: first description of a new species (Chaetonotida, Chaetonotidae, Polymerurus) from an oceanic island with volcanic rocks. European Journal of Taxonomy, 746, 62 - 93. https: // doi. org / ejt. 2021.746.1319" type="journal article" year="2021">
Magpali 
<emphasis box="[822,871,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
